2x+4y&=-17\\
4y&=-2x-17\\
y&=-\frac{1}{2}x-\frac{17}{4}
\end{align*} Therefore, the slope of the given line is $-\frac{1}{2}$. Lines that are parallel to each other have the same slope, so the slope of a line parallel to the given line is also $\boxed{-\frac{1}{2}}$. </think> <answer> $-\frac{1}{2}$ </answer>

