y &= -\frac{1}{2}x-\frac{17}{4}
\end{align*} The slope of the given line is $-\frac{1}{2}$. Parallel lines have the same slope, so the slope of a line parallel to the given line is also $\boxed{-\frac{1}{2}}$. </think> <answer> </answer>

